derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English: from Latin permeabilis, from permeare 'pass through' (see permeate)

entry.def: If a substance is permeable, something such as water or gas can pass through it or soak into it.

example.ex: A number of products have been developed which are permeable to air and water.
example.tran: 已开发出许多可渗水透气的产品。

means.word_mean: 1. allowing (especially liquids) to pass or diffuse through;
